menu "breadboard: bb_tls_info"

config BB_TLS_INFO_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-register TLS capability flags via bb_registry (PRE_HTTP tier)"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_tls_info self-registers at the PRE_HTTP tier and
        calls bb_info_register_capability() for each enabled TLS gate
        (BB_MQTT_TLS_ENABLE → "mqtt_tls", BB_HTTP_TLS_ENABLE → "http_tls",
        BB_TLS_MUTUAL_ENABLE → "mutual_tls").  Must run before bb_info_init
        freezes the capability registry at regular-tier order 2.
        Disable to call bb_tls_info_register() manually.

endmenu
